jupyter_base_url

def jupyter_base_url(

)-&gt;str:

HTTP origin for Jupyter Server (Lab iframe + REST /api/contents).
JUPYTER_BASE_URL wins when set (no trailing slash). Otherwise http://{JUPYTER_HOST}:{JUPYTER_PORT}.
If Jupyter binds to a different port (e.g. it prints http://127.0.0.1:52537 when 8888 is taken), set JUPYTER_BASE_URL to that full origin so the iframe and REST calls match. Default host is 127.0.0.1 to align with opening the app at http://127.0.0.1:ST_PORT.

